<!-- HERO -->
<div class="hero" id="top">
  <div class="hero-bg-text" aria-hidden="true">MARKET</div>
  <div class="hero-tag">Data Justice Project · 2025</div>
  <h1>How Prediction Platforms <em>Commodify</em> Democracy</h1>
  <p class="hero-sub">A data-driven investigation into the hidden power structures, information asymmetries, and social harms embedded in prediction markets like Polymarket and Kalshi.</p>
  <div class="hero-meta">
    <div><span class="hero-meta-label">Markets analyzed</span><span class="hero-meta-val">524</span></div>
    <div><span class="hero-meta-label">Trades in dataset</span><span class="hero-meta-val">3,500</span></div>
    <div><span class="hero-meta-label">Platforms</span><span class="hero-meta-val">Polymarket · Kalshi</span></div>
    <div><span class="hero-meta-label">Team</span><span class="hero-meta-val">Yeung · Carmel · Somani</span></div>
  </div>
  <div class="scroll-hint" aria-hidden="true">Scroll</div>
</div>

<!-- OVERVIEW -->
<div class="w-section" id="overview">
  <div class="w-inner">
    <div class="section-label">Overview</div>
    <h2 class="section-title">The myth of the crowd</h2>
    <div class="intro-grid">
      <div class="intro-lead">Prediction markets promise objectivity — a crowd-sourced oracle immune to bias. But behind the probability curves lies a different reality: thin markets, concentrated power, and populations turned into tradable assets.</div>
      <div class="intro-body">
        <p>Platforms like Polymarket present themselves as neutral aggregators of distributed knowledge. Their pricing data, visualized as smooth curves, tells a story of rational updating and efficient markets.</p>
        <p>Our analysis of 3,500 trades across 524 markets reveals a counter-narrative: just 10 markets capture 50% of all volume. Just 0.5% of trades — the whale tier — control 33% of money. And $21,275 can move in a single second.</p>
        <p>The communities most affected by the events being traded never appear in the dataset at all. Their lives are the stakes; their voices are absent.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="stats-row">
      <div class="stat-card"><div class="stat-number">524</div><div class="stat-label">Markets analyzed</div></div>
      <div class="stat-card"><div class="stat-number">10</div><div class="stat-label">Markets hold 50% of volume</div></div>
      <div class="stat-card"><div class="stat-number">0.5%</div><div class="stat-label">Of trades control 33% of money</div></div>
      <div class="stat-card"><div class="stat-number">67%</div><div class="stat-label">Markets are 80%+ buy-sided</div></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="pull-quote">
  <blockquote>"The data is framed as 'the wisdom of the crowd' — but the crowd is filtered by KYC rules, jurisdictional restrictions, and the need for disposable capital."</blockquote>
  <cite>From the data reflection</cite>
</div>

<!-- VIZ 1: 524 Markets -->
<div class="w-section" id="viz1">
  <div class="w-inner">
    <div class="section-label">Evidence · 01</div>
    <h2 class="section-title">"524 Markets — But Only a Few Matter"</h2>
    <p style="color: var(--muted); font-size: 0.95rem; max-width: 680px;">A power-law distribution governs volume across markets. The top 10 markets capture half of all money — 471 markets split just 20% of the remainder. This is not crowd wisdom; it is structural concentration.</p>
    <div class="viz-block">
      <div class="viz-img-wrap">
        <img src="Screenshot_2026-04-29_at_1_06_28_PM.png" alt="Bar chart showing volume distribution across 524 Polymarket markets. Top 10 markets capture 50% of all volume. Cumulative curve shows rank 53 reaches 80%.">
      </div>
      <p class="viz-caption">Data: Polymarket snapshot (n=3,500 trades, 524 markets). 67% of markets are 80%+ buy-sided — indicating one-directional pressure. The cumulative curve (bottom panel) shows how steeply volume concentrates at the top.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- VIZ 2: 100% Buy Club — LIVE INTERACTIVE -->
<div class="w-section" id="viz2">
  <div class="w-inner">
    <div class="section-label">Evidence · 02</div>
    <h2 class="section-title">The 100% Buy Club</h2>
    <p style="color: var(--muted); font-size: 0.95rem; max-width: 680px;">Markets where 100% of recorded trades are buys have no counterparty — no one is betting the other way. These are not probabilities derived from disagreement; they are single-position assertions dressed up as crowd consensus. Filter and explore the data below.</p>
    <div class="viz-block">
      <div class="interactive-embed-wrap">
        <div class="interactive-embed-header">
          <span class="interactive-badge">Interactive</span>
          <span class="interactive-title">100% Buy Club · Live market explorer — adjust filters to explore</span>
        </div>
        <div class="interactive-body">
          <!-- ========== 100% BUY CLUB WIDGET ========== -->
          <div class="buyclub">
            <h2 class="sr-only">The 100% Buy Club — markets ranked by one-sided pressure and low trade count</h2>
            <div class="header">
              <div class="kpi-grid" id="kpis"></div>
              <div class="controls">
                <label>Min buy %</label>
                <input type="range" min="50" max="100" value="80" step="1" id="minBuy" oninput="document.getElementById('minBuyVal').textContent=this.value+'%';render()">
                <span id="minBuyVal">80%</span>
                <label style="margin-left:12px;">Max trades</label>
                <input type="range" min="1" max="50" value="50" step="1" id="maxTrades" oninput="document.getElementById('maxTradesVal').textContent=this.value;render()">
                <span id="maxTradesVal">50</span>
                <label style="margin-left:12px;">Sort by</label>
                <select id="sortBy" onchange="render()">
                  <option value="buyPct">Buy %</option>
                  <option value="trades">Trade count</option>
                  <option value="volume">Total volume</option>
                  <option value="suspicion">Suspicion score</option>
                </select>
                <label style="margin-left:12px;">Top</label>
                <select id="topN" onchange="render()">
                  <option value="20">20</option>
                  <option value="30">30</option>
                  <option value="50" selected>50</option>
                  <option value="999">All</option>
                </select>
              </div>
              <div class="legend">
                <div class="legend-item"><div class="legend-dot" style="background:#E24B4A;"></div>100% buy (zero sells)</div>
                <div class="legend-item"><div class="legend-dot" style="background:#EF9F27;"></div>90–99% buy</div>
                <div class="legend-item"><div class="legend-dot" style="background:#639922;"></div>&lt;90% buy</div>
              </div>
              <div class="chart-wrap">
                <div style="position:relative;width:100%;height:420px;">
                  <canvas id="mainChart" role="img" aria-label="Horizontal bar chart of markets ranked by one-sided buy pressure"></canvas>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="table-wrap">
              <table>
                <thead>
                  <tr>
                    <th style="width:32px;">#</th>
                    <th style="width:90px;">Market ID</th>
                    <th style="width:70px;">Trades</th>
                    <th style="width:80px;">Buy %</th>
                    <th style="width:90px;">Buy vol</th>
                    <th style="width:90px;">Sell vol</th>
                    <th style="width:120px;">Buy pressure bar</th>
                    <th style="width:90px;">Suspicion</th>
                    <th>Market hash (short)</th>
                  </tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody id="tableBody"></tbody>
              </table>
            </div>
          </div>
          <!-- ========== END WIDGET ========== -->
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class="viz-caption">Data: Polymarket trades snapshot. Each row is one market. "Suspicion score" weights buy-side pressure against trade count — a market with 100% buys and only 1 trade scores higher than one with 90% buys and 40 trades. Use the sliders to filter by minimum buy-side % and maximum trade count.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- VIZ 3: Whale Problem -->
<div class="w-section" id="viz3">
  <div class="w-inner">
    <div class="section-label">Evidence · 03</div>
    <h2 class="section-title">"The Whale Problem" — A Tiny Fraction Controls the Money</h2>
    <p style="color: var(--muted); font-size: 0.95rem; max-width: 680px;">54% of trades are micro transactions under $10 — yet they represent just 5% of volume. Meanwhile, whale trades (over $1,000) make up 0.5% of all transactions but drive 33% of total dollar volume. The crowd votes; the whales decide.</p>
